   <h1>The Troll&#39;s Bane Chronicle</h1>

   <h2>The fourth year of the new era: August</h2>

<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 1st, Val de Gausse pleads for assistance in providing the ransom for Brodir.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 2nd, Caitlin Fergus thanks everyone who had worked together to set herself and Nargon von Largon free. The two had previously been trapped underground due to the occurrence of an unexpected earthquake.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 2nd, Arkadia Misella places a bounty on the elf Callith.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 2nd, Moirear Sian warns the inhabitants of the island of the excessive overexploitation of forests, after noticing the decreased supply of the forest's natural resources.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 3rd, Johann Endan prophesies an upcoming darkness, which may result to the end of time. The island is fortunately spared.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 3rd, a malevolent spirit appears before the eyes Alora Ironforge, Galim, John Irenicus, and Cedric Kilmar. Galim-in turn-forges a holy hammer of righteousness.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 3rd, the Clan of the Axe threatens all those who strive to claim the bounty placed on Dolgan Durgan. Maintaining the alliance between the Clan of the Axe and the Bloodskull Clan is heavily challenged.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 4th, the halfling Ruul Tolfud pleads for his own death. The orc Kruuba grants him this wish.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 4th, the King of Silverbrand-Tialdin-announces that Galim has been given the title, Bishop.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 4th, Trogan Wolfwood warns of pickpockets.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 5th, Kasume warns citizens of intrigues between Ruul Tolfud and Talaena.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 5th, yet another malevolent spirit appears-this time appearing to the dwarves Lorian Lorano and Dolgan Durgan, as well as an orc named Lulufang. The sightings of spirits amass during the next couple of days.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 5th, a scorpion stings Paidraig Baltram. Caitlin Fergus nurses him back to regain good health.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 6th, Boremier returns to the island.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 6th, Irania is released from her imprisonment in jail.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 6th, revenge towards Shukk, on behalf of Konstantin, is anonymously announced.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 6th, Galim announces a conference of the priests in order to discuss the happenings of the past couple of days. The meeting finds moderate attendance.
</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 8th, Gwynnether von Glanwen proposes that the island should be given a name. The procedures go on for weeks from then on.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 10th, Shukk abandons her duty as a Temple Guard of Zelphia.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 10th, Konstantin resurrects his beloved Irania in a dark ritual.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 12th, an unknown person hires followers of Ronagan.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 12th hordes of Trolls attack Troll's Bane. The outcast known as Karmane earns recognition for his role in the defense against the onslaught.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 13th, Domitrio announces that he shall be a priest of Elara from now onward.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 14th, several people warn that leaving the town has proven to be a dangerous decision due to some disturbing events within the last couple of days.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 14th, Ceigan Ibatha warns of the "Magenta Troll of Chaos".</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 16th, Damien announces an important meeting for the elves. Many attend this conference.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 17th, Misjbar officially announces his attempt to become a priest of the five (the five gods / goddesses).</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 17th, Sian warns of a monster inducing fear and terror. At the same time, Caitlin Fergus warns of a severe epidemic.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 18th, Vilarion announces publicly that he seeks an alchemist.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 20th, Ceigan Ibatha warns of an attack by the Magenta Troll. Numerous reports of the subject ensue.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 22nd, the election for the five members of the Elven Council commences.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 23rd, the Clan of the Axe invites everyone to a day of beer and excavations.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 23rd, Willum announces a threat going out to all those who clear the forest.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 24th, Bronzebeard reports that Alora has slain him.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 26th, Aristeaus founds a guild named "The Concubius." Their goals are the resettlement of the north, providing help for those in need, and the enforcement of equilibrium for power.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 27th, Lennier initiates a contest to discover the recipe for antidote potions. Burlow Boinclod is the winner of the 10 ingots and a rare mushroom.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 28th, Vurhel looks for a teacher of martial arts.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 28th, Malvita is on the lookout for inhabitants who can inform him of the history of the island.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 31st, Irania admits to have beaten Talaena down twice within town limits, and awaits the town guard's judgment.</p>
<p>In the year 4 of the new era on August the 31st, the noble knight Lennier is given the title "Earl of the Grey Rose".</p>


